 <text>
  <front>
   <head>On the Death of André.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1">
     <l n="1">Nature shrinks back, in agony of grief</l>
     <l n="2">Deep felt.</l>
     <l n="3">Washington, that deed of thine,</l>
     <l n="4">I write it desperate.</l>
     <l n="5">Unpassioned souls, in ages yet unborn,</l>
     <l n="6">Will read it different.</l>
     <l n="7">Cruel,</l>
     <l n="8">Unnatural war, by Heaven sent,</l>
     <l n="9">To rouse the nobler powers,</l>
     <l n="10">Absorb'd in luxury,</l>
     <l n="11">Or vice</l>
     <l n="12">Licentious.</l>
     <l n="13">Proud nations. Love of liberty carried too far.</l>
     <l n="14">One of your noblest — bravest — dearest sons</l>
     <l n="15">Dies!</l>
     <l n="16">To reunite you.</l>
     <l n="17">Relent.</l>
     <l n="18">Oh my heart bleeds — bursts with grief.</l>
     <l n="19">Regret.</l>
     <l n="20">Calm to the last — what energy</l>
     <l n="21">Of worth!</l>
     <l n="22">Thousands are animate</l>
     <l n="23">Beheld thy glorious death</l>
     <l n="24">Silent!</l>
     <l n="25">Or with averted eye — scarce look</l>
     <l n="26">On — Washington.</l>
     <l n="27">Death,</l>
     <l n="28">'Tis immortality.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
